crap, that's not right either.

while (0) { __ALOGV(..) } doesn't work because if (x) ALOGV(...); else ALOGV(...); gets an extra semicolon after the while (0), which breaks the if.

I think this will work:
do { if (0) { __ALOGV(__VA_ARGS__); } } while (0)

